$ ADO/VBA examples for Oracle: Transaction management

The following example tries to demonstrate how → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/transaction[transactions] can be used in an
→ development/databases/ADO[ADO]/→ development/languages/VBA combination.

gh|about-adodb|/Oracle/transaction/func.vb||

Executing this example prints the following output:
code {
After writing data without transaction
  inserted with autocommit
After writing data within transactions
  inserted with autocommit
  commited record
After commiting transaction
  inserted with autocommit
  commited record
  commited or rolled back?
code }

{ Creating the example from command line

  The following → development/languages/VBScript file can be used in conjunction with the
  → Microsoft/Office/VBScript-App-Creator to create an → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook[Excel workbook] in which the
  example can be executed.

  gh|about-adodb|/Oracle/transaction/create.wsf||

}

sa:

  → development/databases/ADO/objects/connection/transaction

  → development/databases/ADO/ADODB-examples/Oracle
